{"id":22965,"title":"N-Methyl and peptoid scans of an autoinducing peptide reveal new structural features required for inhibition and activation of AgrC quorum sensing receptors in Staphylococcus aureus.","abstract":"We report the first N-methyl and peptoid residue scans of a full-length autoinducing peptide (AIP), AIP-III, used by Staphylococcus aureus for quorum sensing (QS). Biological evaluation of these AIP-III analogues uncovered new features of the AIP-III scaffold that can be tuned to develop chemical probes of QS in all four groups of S. aureus (I-IV). ","date":"2014-02-20","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24509706","annotations":[{"name":"Receptor (biochemistry)","weight":0.81434,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Receptor_(biochemistry)"},{"name":"Peptide","weight":0.740492,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peptide"},{"name":"Quorum sensing","weight":0.731221,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quorum_sensing"},{"name":"Enzyme inhibitor","weight":0.573145,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enzyme_inhibitor"},{"name":"Staphylococcus aureus","weight":0.554085,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus_aureus"},{"name":"Staphylococcus","weight":0.323844,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staphylococcus"},{"name":"Chemical substance","weight":0.28582,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemical_substance"},{"name":"Structure","weight":0.222533,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Structure"},{"name":"Biology","weight":0.168449,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biology"},{"name":"Regulation of gene expression","weight":0.163731,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulation_of_gene_expression"},{"name":"Scaffolding","weight":0.111906,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scaffolding"},{"name":"Quorum","weight":0.0297972,"wiki